CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 24, 1954, pg. 11, reads: "Alpha Picnic - As usual the Alpha picnic attracted a large crowd of fun-lovers who responded to the clever invitations sent out by the members of the fraternity, by taking them up on their invite to spend a day with Robin Hood in Sherwood's Forest.. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of seven Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity members wearing Robin Hood style costumes, gathered on lawn for Alpha picnic, North Park
